I"A<p>Besides implying <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/experientialism-breaks-the-subjectivism-objectivism-dichotomy">the existence of a physical self independent of an absolute ground</a>, the interoception-exteroception distinction highlights the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cortical-subcortical-conflict-generates-limbic-friction">conflicting nature of perceiving the body and the environment</a>. The saliency of one of them modulates the resources deployed to the other. The control of this “budget” is influenced by the quality of sleep.</p>
